today, and it is flown regularly by the RSA .The russian lunar launch vehicle was also built. It was fueled by kerosine, and<br>
oxygen.The successful soyuz launch vehicle also uses these same fuels.The origional, and failed Russian moon rcket  was called the N-1.<br>
<br>
 The N-1 kept blowing up on the  launch pad  and it was abandoned  in 1971. The N-1 was replaced by the Energia in the 1980s ,  which  was successful, at putting 100 tons<br>
 in leo..The russain Lem (lunar lander)  was built but it was  never used because of the failure of the N-1 launch vehicle  .<br>
 Today it is an exchibit in the the Russian mueseum of cosmanautucs.<br>
