n class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/Bart-term.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Real space battles</span><hr size=1> Of course the very concept of the dogfight may become obsolete...<br>
If as is the case with the F-14's Phoenix missile, you can engage 6<br>
seperate targets at ranges of 120 kilometers, well beyond visual <br>
range, then all the dogfighting skills in the world won't save you.<br>
<br>
How much dogfighting actually took place in the Gulf War?  Very little.<br>
The Soviet built Iraqi Air Force was out numbered by superior aircraft<br>
and tactics.<br>
<br>
Of course during the Vietnam war it was believed that the dogfight<br>
was obsolete... the US Air Force entered the F-4 Phantom into the war <br>
with a missile system but no gun for dogfighting.  The F-4 suffered <br>
serious losses against Soviet Migs until pilots were given a F-4 with <br>
a gun and dogfight training. Kill ratios shot up after that.<br>
<br>
But that was over 30 years ago and missile technology and tracking have<br>
improved... the last hope for the continuation of the classic<br>
dogfight is Stealth technology... you have to see it to kill it<br>
mentality. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=x@nuclearspace>X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 187<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/15/02 2:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=379.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/Bart-term.gif" align=absmiddle>  Real space battles</span><hr size=1> zaphod wrote:<br>
